{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:13:04.502753+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here are the setup and day-to-day development commands for this Vue.js 3 Vite starter template repository:\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- **Node.js**: v24 (specified in `.nvmrc`)\n- **Package Manager**: pnpm 10.20.0 (enforced via `preinstall` script)\n\n## Install Dependencies\n\n```bash\npnpm install\n```\n\n## Development Commands\n\n| Command | Script | Description |\n|---------|--------|-------------|\n| `pnpm run dev` | `vite` | Start development server with hot-reload |\n| `pnpm run build` | `vite build` | Build for production |\n| `pnpm run preview` | `vite preview` | Preview production build locally |\n| `pnpm run build-preview` | `vite build && vite preview` | Build and preview in one step |\n| `pnpm run test:unit` | `vitest` | Run unit tests in watch mode |\n| `pnpm run test:unit-coverage` | `vitest run --coverage` | Run unit tests with coverage report |\n| `pnpm run lint` | `eslint \"**/*.{vue,ts,js}\"` | Lint all Vue, TypeScript, and JavaScript files |\n| `pnpm run lint-fix` | `eslint --fix \"**/*.{vue,ts,js}\"` | Lint and auto-fix issues |\n| `pnpm run prepare` | `husky` | Set up Husky git hooks |\n\n## Additional Tools\n\n- **ESLint**: Linting with custom config (`@kouts/eslint-config`)\n- **Prettier**: Code formatting (`prettier.config.js`)\n- **Commitlint**: Conventional commit messages enforced via Husky pre-commit hooks\n- **Lint-staged**: Runs linters on staged files before commit", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 417, "prompt_tokens": 8739, "total_tokens": 9156, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 32, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8576, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details